 "name": "RPlog_Visitations_from_Obi-Wan",
 "title": "Visitations from Obi-Wan: A Master's Doubt",
 "summary": "In Ben Kenobi's old hut on Tatooine, Luke Skywalker begins training Jessalyn as a Jedi, telling her she must construct her own lightsaber--starting with the difficult task of fabricating a focusing crystal from leftover materials and a cryptic instruction book. As the tech-minded Jessalyn skeptically pores over the manual, Luke is suddenly gripped by fear of failing as a teacher and haunted by visions of his student falling to darkness. The spirit of Obi-Wan Kenobi manifests, sensed but unseen by Jessalyn, and gently counsels Luke that fear gains power only when indulged, that the Light is no weaker than the Dark, and that he must trust the Force and act in the present rather than dwell on caution. Reassured, Luke affirms that he is ready and that the time to revive the Jedi is now, as Ben's presence fades back into the Force.",
